                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Updated proposal based on review feedback. Key changes:\n1. Fire-and-forget presence emission to avoid blocking MCP handlers\n2. Dual-layer throttle: client-side 500ms + server-side 2s dedup\n3. PixelCanvas sprite system with deterministic color assignment\n4. Redis pub/sub for multi-instance propagation with in-memory fallback\n5. Ephemeral 3-second indicators prevent stale presence ghost artifacts\n6. Zero-effort detection from MCP tool parameters — agents don't need to explicitly emit presence",
                      "lineHeight": 1.5,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 13,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
